history.text: Hey! Ready to start?
This was a great movie where the toys pretended to be lifeless until their owners were gone.
Yes! It was. I feel like Tom Hanks did a very good job as Woody.
Yes, and Tim Allen as Buzz Lightyear was awesome.
I see that it received high rankings on Rotten Tomatoes, Metacritic, and CinemaScore. I agree with those! I think it was a great movie.
Yeah, it did well. I think it is a work of genius. It really made people understand what toys are all about.
The critical response was also really positive. I think it started a whole new era for Pixar / Disney, and CG animation as a whole.
Yeah, and the musical score by Randy Newman was really great too.
I completely forgot about the music until you just mentioned it. :) It's quite iconic.
Very much so!
I never knew this, but according to the info I have here, it was executive-produced by Steve Jobs.
Interesting, I'm not sure about that. But the director was John Lasseter.
Yeah. I don't know if John went on to direct the following Toy Story movies, but he did an incredible job with this one.
He really did. Did you know that Andy, to boy who owns the toys, last name was Davis?
Hah! I didn't. That's cool.
It was such a great plot point that Buzz really thought he was a space ranger.
I wonder if they directly worked with kids to get ideas of how children would see toys and the world around them from that perspective?
Don't know about that, could have been. But it does show real world experiences like how Woody started to feel lonely when the other toys took a liking to Buzz.
That's true. Man, what a good movie.
I'm remembering all of the secondary characters now, too. I really liked Mr. Potato Head and Rex.

Yeah. And what a great bad guy
 Sid was!
He really typified the sort of sociopathic, child bully character.
I think it is true what the Critics say that it is a hallmark of the greatest child movies of all time.
Absolutely. I watched it as a child and it stuck with me for so long.
The chase at the end where they are trying to get onto the moving truck! So exciting!
I had forgotten about that. Buzz "flies" correctly for the first time.
Any Woody is using the AC car to save Buzz but the other toys think he is trying to hurt AC, so funny.
I guess this is in the back of my head somewhere, but it was the first feature-length CG film.
Oh really? Hard to believe it was made all the way back in 1995.
Have a good day!
bye
